{
  "stem": "11611.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Baron Louis Rothschild was the head of the Paris branch of the Rothschild family.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By this time, he wasn't so Jewish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, the Rothschilds had intermarried for so many generations since Napoleon that he was maybe a quarter, or a fourth, or an eighth-- an eighth Jewish, and had, of course, a title of French nobility, like a fair number of Jews in Europe-- German nobility.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the Germans seized Louis Rothschild in Paris.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Rothschild family owned one of the most modern steel processing plants in Czechoslovakia, which was on the Polish border, known as Vitkovice-- very modern.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Germans, of course, seized it as soon as they entered Czechoslovakia, but they wanted legal title.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That, they could only get-- the Germans liked legal titles.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They weren't content merely to grab.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They liked to force the owners to turn stuff over to them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They had him in a Paris hotel, and both Rasche and Kehrl, Ministry of Economics guy, were negotiating with him.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I put the word 'negotiating' in quotes because one of their negotiating techniques was to invoke the Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Louis Rothschild wasn't a total fool.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He had a pretty good idea what his negotiating position was.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I think he finally made a deal to turn over the stock certificates to the Vitkovice plant-- which is what the Germans wanted, what the Dresdner Bank wanted-- in exchange for getting out of the country alive.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And it was a remarkable transaction, not in that the Germans got the plant, but he actually did get out alive.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That was what was remarkable.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Germans were not all that good in keeping faith on these kinds of contracts.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had no interest in Rothschild.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was an episode in my case.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
